        </tr>
        <tr class="row-total">
          <td>Present Value of Terminal Value</td>
          <td class="highlight-cell">${pvTerminalValue.toLocaleString()}</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>

  <!-- BRINGING IT ALL TOGETHER -->
  <h2>Enterprise & Equity Value</h2>
  <p>We add the present value of Phase 1 to the terminal value to get the Enterprise Value (the value of the core operations). Then we adjust for the balance sheet to find what the equity is worth.</p>

  <div class="table-wrap">
    <table>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td>PV of Phase 1 Cash Flows</td>
          <td>${pvPhase1.toLocaleString()}</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>PV of Terminal Value</td>
          <td>${pvTerminalValue.toLocaleString()}</td>
        </tr>
        <tr class="row-total">
          <td>Enterprise Value</td>
